def: Of or pertaining to a chloride; containing a chloride.
To thrive poorly; to be not thrifty or prosperous. [Obs.]

A device, consisting essentially of an electric arc and acamera, by which a series of photographs of the variations of the arcdue to sound waves are obtained for reproduction by means of aselenium cell and a telephone.
A mean or inferior poet, perhaps from his habit of wanderingaround as a stroller; an itinerant poet. Also, a name given to thecyclic poets. See under Cyclic, a. [Obs.] B. Jonson.
A small narrow opening or window in a tower or fortified wall;a loophole.
Affording, or disposed to afford, accommodation; obliging; asan accommodating man, spirit, arrangement.
An iodide containing a higher proportion of iodine than anyother iodide of the same substance or series.
A genus of shrubs and trees, mostly American or Asiatic,abounding in resinous and aromatic substances. Styrax officinalisyields storax, and S. Benzoin yields benzoin.
Antagonistic to one's country or nation, or to a nationalgovernment.
